✅ Question 2: Amazon Prime Subscriptions
📦 Class: Amazonprime
Attributes:

int primeId

String userName

int subscribedPackage (in days)

String showStreaming

int views

➡️ Implement:

All attributes should be private

Create getters, setters, and a parameterized constructor

📘 Class: Solution
Implement two static methods:

🔹 Method 1: findRemainingSubscriptionDays
Inputs:

Array of Amazonprime objects

int days

int primeId

Output:

Return subscribedPackage - days if primeId is found

If not found, return 0

🔸 In main():

If return value > 0 → print the number

If return value = 0 → print:

css
Copy
Edit
Its time to recharge your Prime Account
🔹 Method 2: findDetailsForGivenShow
Inputs:

Array of Amazonprime objects

String show (case-insensitive)

Output:

Return Amazonprime[] filtered where showStreaming matches the input

Sort by views in ascending order

If none found → return null

🔸 In main():

If null → print:

arduino
Copy
Edit
No such shows available
Else → print in format:

shell
Copy
Edit
primeId$userName$views
🧪 Sample Input Pattern:
css
Copy
Edit
100
April
129
